docs.abstract: Twitter said a tweet by Mr. Jones violated its rules against inciting violence. The move was Twitter’s harshest against Mr. Jones and his company.
docs.snippet: Twitter said a tweet by Mr. Jones violated its rules against inciting violence. The move was Twitter’s harshest against Mr. Jones and his company.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Twitter on Tuesday suspended the account of the far-right conspiracy theorist Alex Jones for a week after he tweeted a link to a video calling for supporters to get their “battle rifles” ready against media and others, in a violation of the company’s rules against inciting violence.

headline.main: Twitter Suspends Alex Jones and Infowars for Seven Days
headline.print_headline: Twitter Suspends Infowars Founder’s Account Over a Tweet

docs.abstract: Every two years, voters — whether they already count on the program, expect to or question paying into it — try to make sense of competing claims about it. It’s that time again.
docs.snippet: Every two years, voters — whether they already count on the program, expect to or question paying into it — try to make sense of competing claims about it. It’s that time again.
docs.lead_paragraph: It’s no wonder that Social Security is politically contentious. The program’s reach is vast: More than 175 million workers contribute to it with every paycheck, and about 43 million retirees collect monthly benefits. For three in five older Americans, those checks account for more than half their income.

headline.main: 8 Questions About Social Security Answered as Election Day Nears
headline.print_headline: As the Political Rhetoric Heats Up, A Social Security Guide for the Ages

docs.abstract: Microsoft workers objected to the company’s work with immigration authorities, part of a wave of outrage over the Trump administration’s immigration policy.
docs.snippet: Microsoft workers objected to the company’s work with immigration authorities, part of a wave of outrage over the Trump administration’s immigration policy.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — In an open letter posted to Microsoft’s internal message board on Tuesday, more than 100 employees protested the software maker’s work with Immigration and Customs Enforcement and asked the company to stop working with the agency, which has been separating migrant parents and their children at the border with Mexico.

headline.main: Microsoft Employees Protest Work With ICE, as Tech Industry Mobilizes Over Immigration
